    "summary": "As a strategic advisor in the field of fiscal and financial-economic criminality, I work on combatting illicit financial flows both domestically and internationally. I bridge the gap between ad-hoc law enforcement needs and strategic long-term thinking, while staying sensitive for (inter)national cultures, changing environments and new challenges. \n\nPreviously, I have coordinated the evaluation of the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) against money laundering and terrorist financing from the Dutch Ministry of Justice and Security, as well as other international relations such as the European Commission and the Council of Europe Warsaw Convention, the latter to which I currently still contribute as a Board Member. \n\nI gained professional experience in the same field as a legal/political programme assistant at MONEYVAL, the Council of Europe division on anti-money laundering and countering the financing of terrorism. I also took up large responsibilities for the work output of the Conference of the Parties of the 2005 Council of Europe Warsaw Convention (CETS no. 198) on AML/CFT matters.",
